<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-07T01:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-07T01:30:00-05:00" n="1160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1160">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/212</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WCS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-07T09:00:00+02:30">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Urgent. Austrian Ambassador and staff have left. In view of destruction
                            German Embassy and fearing same Austrian Embassy, am I authorized to
                            raise thereon American flag if I judge it necessary to save Embassy
                            premises and lives of occupants?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WCS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>